Quite scarcely documented. Sampled in brooklet and in stagnant remain of brooklet and in a rain pool (van Vondel 2005 ). Label data give that the species has been collected from a stream from hot springs in Sudan. Additionally labels tell that the species was collected from slowly running stream, from a stream in dry forest and from a rock pool. Also collected at light or with light traps. Some information on biology can also be gained from Omer-Cooper (1958b) . In Socotra Island, Yemen, the species was mostly collected in larger pools of drying up streams in wadis (
Hajek and Reiter 2014
).
